	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just thought I'd put my 2cp in..<br>I was in L guk, the night before today, with a friend, 54 mage, who was camping the RC for my birthday, Lord Group trains the Lord and others on us, we nearly finish them but both die. We come back and find that Magi is supposedly uncamped, so we start to head that way, someone says it camped as we near the doorway, so we head back to Sage.. Another group has already set in, not a problem except that we were moving to magi 'unless it's camped', so we go back to sage anyway, in the end a GM is called and roll random to see who stays, we loose roll and leave, yay. Next day, get up around 9 and hop on to see if I can get in a group to get my own RC, long story short, it's the last spawn after about 5 deaths thanks to stupidity on the most part and 1 comp crash.. Last spawn is sage, sage goes down, I loot, it has an RC, so I pick it up.. This is the worst part of all, I am an enc with about 172 int, the rc would easily be far better than my Savant's cap, but NO, the rogue, the druid, and both paladins in the group just -have- to have it, rolled 5 to 500 lowest, I got a 50, druid gets a 8, naturally.. To this day I have literally never won a roll, love you too Verant :p<br>And the druid already has 198 wis and can't use it anyway, I just love ethics these days.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
